+8. Security Model
+8.1 Data Isolation
+The takeovers-cos project is fully separate from the Takeovers Unified Platform. No shared database, no shared deployment, no shared API keys. A bug in either system cannot affect the other. Customer-facing data (booking records, customer PII) does not flow into the CoS agent.
+8.2 Authentication
+	•	PWA: single-user auth (Clerk or Auth0), 2FA required, session timeout at 30 days
+	•	Gmail accounts: OAuth 2.0 per account, refresh tokens encrypted at rest
+	•	Twilio: API key in env vars, separate keys per environment
+	•	Claude API: separate keys per environment, usage capped per environment
+	•	GitHub: Personal access token, read-only scopes initially
+	•	Google Drive/Calendar: OAuth scoped to least privilege
+8.3 Secrets Management
+All secrets in environment variables. No secrets in code, no secrets in commits, no secrets in logs. Replit's secrets manager holds production values. Local development uses a .env file that is gitignored.
+8.4 Kill Switches
+	•	Global kill switch in PWA settings (drops to Tier B-only mode)
+	•	Per-channel kill switches (disable email send, disable SMS send independently)
+	•	Per-account kill switch for each Gmail account
+	•	Feature flags on every agent capability for surgical rollback
+8.5 Audit Trail
+Every agent action — every SMS sent, every email drafted or sent, every task dispatched, every follow-up triggered, every escalation — is logged with timestamp, recipient, content, and the input that caused it. Logs are retained indefinitely and searchable from the Insights tab.
+8.6 Backups
+Daily automated backups of the production Postgres to S3 (or Replit's backup service). Retained 30 days rolling, plus weekly snapshots retained 90 days. Recovery procedure documented in the Build Environment Setup Guide.
+9. Companion Documents
+This master spec is supplemented by the following documents, each living in the takeovers-cos repo at /docs:
+	•	02 — Database Schema Doc. Full Postgres schema with column definitions, relationships, and indexes.
+	•	03 — Build Environment Setup Guide. Three-environment setup (local / staging / production), git workflow, feature flags, migrations, backups, deployment configuration.
+	•	04–10 — Phase Build Docs. One per build phase. Each covers what to build, how to test, acceptance criteria, and dependencies.
+	•	Diagrams. System architecture diagram, data flow diagram, agent decision tree, deployment diagram.
+10. Open Decisions
+These remain open and should be revisited during build:
+	•	Whether to use Clerk or Auth0 for PWA auth (both work; Clerk is faster to set up)
+	•	Whether to use BullMQ for background jobs or do everything in n8n (likely both — n8n for high-level loops, BullMQ for tight scheduling)
+	•	Whether to integrate the Insights tab with Selmen's calendar to schedule weekly review time automatically
+	•	Whether the agent should have voice output (call back, voicemail) in a future phase
+	•	Whether to expose the agent to Brandon and Richard as a shared tool, or keep it strictly Selmen-only (recommended: Selmen-only for v1)
+This document is the umbrella. Companion documents 02–10 contain the specific schemas, build instructions, and deployment configuration needed to actually build the system. Read this first, then read the companion documents in order.
