+Overview
+This document defines the complete database schema for the takeovers-cos agent. Every table, column, type, constraint, index, and relationship is specified here. The schema is implemented in Postgres using Drizzle ORM for type-safe queries and migration management.
+The schema is organized into seven logical groups:
+	•	1. Core Identity — team members and the principal (Selmen) himself
+	•	2. Communication — conversation threads, messages, the continuous Talk thread
+	•	3. Tasks & Projects — the work the agent dispatches and tracks
+	•	4. Follow-up — the chase scheduler that prevents drops
+	•	5. Email — the three Gmail accounts and their messages
+	•	6. Learning — logs, SOPs, insights, patterns the agent has identified
+	•	7. System — feature flags, audit trail, configuration
+Every table includes created_at and updated_at timestamps managed by Drizzle. Every primary key is a UUID v4 unless noted. Soft deletes (deleted_at) are used for anything a human has touched — hard deletes only for system-internal tables.
