+Why This Document Exists First
+Before a single agent feature is built, the build environment must be locked down. The reason is simple: the worst possible bug in this system is not a crash — it is the agent texting Brandon's lawyer something half-formed at 2 AM, or sending Orlando a fake task about fleet repair, or auto-archiving an email from Karina that needed Selmen's eyes.
+Staging exists so every loop in the agent — capture, dispatch, chase, briefing — can be tested end-to-end against fake recipients before a single byte hits a real team member. Feature flags exist so a misbehaving capability can be killed in seconds without a redeploy. Backups exist because the agent's database is Selmen's second brain and losing it is unacceptable.
+If you skip this setup and start building features against production directly, you will burn team trust the first time the agent misfires. Set up the three environments first. Always.
+
+1. The Three Environments
+Environment
