+1.1 What each environment has independently
+Every environment has its own copy of every external dependency. Nothing is shared except the source code itself.
+	•	Database — separate Postgres instance per environment
+	•	Twilio number — separate phone number for SMS sends, so test messages cannot reach real team
+	•	Gmail OAuth — staging hits a test Gmail account; production hits the real three accounts
+	•	Claude API key — separate keys per environment to track usage and prevent staging tests from blowing prod budget
+	•	Whisper API key — same logic — separate keys
+	•	Environment variables — every secret scoped to its environment, never shared
+	•	n8n instance — if running self-hosted n8n, separate instance per environment
+	•	Storage bucket — separate S3 bucket (or Replit storage) per environment for voice memos and attachments
+The cost of running three environments is real but small — roughly $30-40/month extra for staging beyond what production costs. The cost of NOT running staging is one bad message to a partner. The math is obvious.
