+2.2 Why a monorepo
+PWA, API, database schema, and shared types all evolve together. A monorepo means a schema change ships in the same commit as the API code that uses it and the PWA code that displays it. Use pnpm workspaces or npm workspaces — pnpm is faster but either works.
+2.3 What goes in /docs
+Drop all 13 documents from this set into the /docs folder of the repo. The agent itself can later be pointed at this folder via GitHub API to ground its own decisions in its own architecture. This is the reference Selmen uploads on Day 1 of the build.
