+3. Git Workflow
+3.1 Branch model
+	•	main — production. Auto-deploys to cos.takeoversrentals.com. Protected: never push directly. PRs only.
+	•	staging — staging environment. Auto-deploys to staging.cos.takeoversrentals.com. PRs from feature branches merge here first.
+	•	feature/* — work in progress. e.g. feature/voice-capture, feature/email-drafts, feature/escalation-logic.
+3.2 Daily workflow
+	•	Start a feature: create a branch off staging — git checkout staging && git pull && git checkout -b feature/whatever
+	•	Build it locally. Run against your local Postgres + Redis.
+	•	Push the branch. Open a PR to staging.
+	•	Replit auto-deploys staging when the PR is merged. Test the feature on staging.cos.takeoversrentals.com against the shadow team.
+	•	Once staging passes, open a PR from staging to main. Merge.
+	•	Replit auto-deploys main to production. Watch the logs for 15 minutes. Done.
+3.3 Commit hygiene
+	•	Conventional commits: feat:, fix:, chore:, docs:, refactor:, test:
+	•	Never commit .env files (gitignored by default)
+	•	Never commit secrets — even in test/seed data, use placeholders
+	•	Squash-merge PRs to main to keep history clean
+3.4 Branch protection rules (set on GitHub)
+	•	main: require PR review (self-review acceptable since you're the only dev), require staging deploy to succeed, require status checks passing
+	•	staging: require PR (no direct push), allow self-merge
