+6. Feature Flags
+Feature flags are the surgical rollback mechanism. Every agent capability sits behind a flag. Flags live in the feature_flags table (defined in Document 02) and have a UI toggle in the PWA settings.
+6.1 Flag-driven rollout pattern
+When you ship a new agent capability, you ship the code with the flag OFF. You verify it deploys without error, then flip the flag in production. If it misbehaves, you flip the flag OFF and the capability is instantly disabled — no redeploy, no downtime, no rollback commits.
+6.2 Code pattern
+In the API code, every flag-gated capability is wrapped:
+// services/dispatch.ts
+import { isEnabled } from '@/lib/flags';
+
+export async function dispatchTask(task) {
+  if (!await isEnabled('auto_dispatch_internal_team')) {
+    // Flag is off — drop to draft mode regardless of tier
+    return queueForApproval(task);
+  }
+  // Flag on — proceed with autonomous dispatch
+  return sendTask(task);
+}
+6.3 Initial seed flags (also documented in Schema doc)
