+11. Monitoring & Observability
+You need to know when the agent is misbehaving without having to read every log entry.
+11.1 What to monitor
+	•	API health (uptime, response times, error rates)
+	•	Background job queue depth (if BullMQ is backing up, follow-ups will be late)
+	•	Twilio send failures (network issues, throttling, invalid numbers)
+	•	Gmail API errors (token expiry, rate limits)
+	•	Claude API errors (timeouts, rate limits, malformed responses)
+	•	Override rate (% of agent actions that Selmen edits or rejects — sudden spike means agent quality is dropping)
+11.2 Recommended tools
+	•	Sentry — free tier covers everything you need. Catches all uncaught exceptions, ranks by frequency. Set up on Day 1.
+	•	Replit's built-in logs — real-time stdout/stderr from the API. Sufficient for the first few months.
+	•	Insights tab dashboard — the Learning loop already tracks override rate. Surface it in the Insights tab so you see weekly trends.
+	•	BullMQ board — an admin route that shows queue health. Auth-gated to Selmen only.
+11.3 Critical alerts (push to Selmen via SMS)
+These need to wake you up. Configure them as immediate SMS alerts to Selmen's phone:
+	•	Production API down for more than 60 seconds
+	•	Database connection lost
+	•	Twilio webhook failing repeatedly (means inbound team responses aren't being captured)
+	•	Gmail OAuth refresh failed (means email integration is broken)
+	•	Claude API down or repeatedly erroring
+11.4 Non-critical observations (surface in PWA Insights tab)
+	•	Override rate trending up week-over-week
+	•	Specific team member's response time degrading
+	•	Cost spike on Claude API
+	•	Storage bucket approaching size limit
+
+12. Pre-Launch Security Checklist
+Run through this before flipping any production flag from OFF to ON. Print it, check it off.
+12.1 Secrets
+	•	All API keys live only in Replit secrets and local .env (gitignored)
+	•	ENCRYPTION_KEY is generated, stored in Replit secrets, backed up to 1Password
+	•	OAuth refresh tokens are encrypted at rest using ENCRYPTION_KEY before insert
+	•	WEBHOOK_SECRET is set and validated on inbound n8n webhooks
+	•	No secret has ever been committed to git (run git log -p | grep -i 'sk-' to verify)
+12.2 Auth
+	•	PWA requires login (Clerk or Auth0)
+	•	2FA enabled on Selmen's PWA account
+	•	Session timeout configured (30 days max)
+	•	API endpoints require auth except /health and webhook receivers
+	•	Webhook receivers validate HMAC signatures
+12.3 Network
+	•	HTTPS enforced (Let's Encrypt via Replit, no HTTP fallback)
+	•	CORS configured to allow only the PWA's origin
+	•	Rate limiting on public endpoints (e.g. login, OAuth callbacks)
+12.4 Data
+	•	Database is in a private Replit instance, not publicly accessible
+	•	Postgres uses SSL connections
+	•	S3 bucket has private ACL, no public access
+	•	Backups are encrypted at rest
+12.5 Code
+	•	Dependencies up to date (pnpm audit shows 0 high/critical)
+	•	No console.log of sensitive data (tokens, OAuth codes, message contents in error paths)
+	•	Error messages to PWA don't leak stack traces in production
+	•	All user input that hits Claude is rate-limited per user (no infinite voice memo loop)
+Run this checklist before going live. Run it again every 90 days. Security is not a one-time setup — it's a habit.
+
+13. The Go-Live Sequence
+When Phase 1 is built and tested in staging, here's the order to go live in production.
+13.1 The week before
+	•	Run the security checklist (Section 12)
+	•	Run a full backup restore drill
+	•	Verify all production secrets are set in Replit
+	•	Verify production Twilio number is provisioned and tested with a manual SMS
+	•	Verify production Gmail OAuth connections are working for all three accounts
+	•	Confirm cos.takeoversrentals.com DNS is set and SSL is provisioned
+13.2 Launch day
+	•	Merge staging → main, watch the deploy
+	•	Run the migrations against production (auto-runs on deploy)
+	•	Seed production with the real team_members data
+	•	Log into the production PWA, verify the Today tab loads
+	•	Send a test message to yourself via the production agent number — verify it routes correctly
+	•	Verify all feature flags are OFF (default state)
+13.3 First two weeks
+	•	Day 1-3: only Talk and Today tabs active. Verify capture is working. No dispatch, no follow-up, no email.
+	•	Day 4-7: enable email reading (no replies, no archives). Verify the Inbox tab populates correctly.
+	•	Week 2: enable auto_email_archive flag. Verify newsletters get archived as expected. Spot-check 10 archives manually.
+	•	Week 2 end: enable auto_dispatch_internal_team for the lowest-stakes team member first (likely Tahir or Joan). Watch the first few dispatches manually.
+13.4 Progressive rollout
+	•	Week 3: enable dispatch for Oscar, Josh, Orlando
+	•	Week 4: enable dispatch for Nick (with detailed style)
+	•	Week 4: enable auto_followup_nudge_1
+	•	Week 5: enable auto_followup_nudge_2
+	•	Week 6: enable auto_email_reply_internal for low-confidence-threshold replies only
+	•	Beyond week 6: gradual increase in confidence threshold for auto-reply, gradual broadening of dispatch authority
+NEVER turn on multiple flags simultaneously in production. One at a time, with at least 48 hours between flips, so you can attribute any misbehavior to a specific change.
