+TAKEOVERS CHIEF OF STAFF
+Phase 1
+PWA Shell + Capture
+Document 04 of 13
+Estimated build time: 2-3 weeks
+Outcome: Selmen captures every thought through voice or text. Nothing is lost.
+
+Phase Goal
+Phase 1 delivers the smallest possible system that produces real value: continuous capture. Selmen can voice-memo or text the agent at any time, the agent transcribes and structures the input, stores it, and surfaces a daily brief. Nothing else exists yet — no dispatch, no follow-up, no email handling, no team communication.
+This phase is the foundation. By the end of it, Selmen has replaced his "never write down the to-do list" habit with a system that captures everything. That alone solves a meaningful portion of the day-to-day pain — and gives him a working surface to iterate on before adding more powerful (and riskier) capabilities.
+What you can do at the end of Phase 1:
+	•	Open the PWA on phone or desktop, log in
+	•	Tap a voice button, speak a brain-dump, see it transcribed and structured
+	•	Text the agent's Twilio number — same flow
+	•	View the Today tab — daily brief, prioritized to-do list
+	•	Tap any captured item to expand, edit, or mark done
+	•	Receive a morning and evening brief automatically
+What is explicitly NOT in this phase:
+	•	No dispatch to team members (Phase 2)
+	•	No follow-up scheduler (Phase 4)
+	•	No email integration (Phase 3)
+	•	No projects, insights, file access (later phases)
+
+1. What to Build
+1.1 The PWA Shell
+A React + Vite PWA with the seven-tab navigation laid out. Only Tab 1 (Talk) and Tab 2 (Today) are functional in Phase 1. The other five tabs exist as empty placeholders — this avoids restructuring the navigation later.
+Tabs and their Phase 1 status
+Tab
+Phase 1 status
+Notes
+Talk
+FULLY FUNCTIONAL
+Voice + text input, continuous thread
+Today
+FULLY FUNCTIONAL
+Daily brief, captured tasks list
+Approvals
+Placeholder
+Empty state: "Nothing pending"
+Inbox
+Placeholder
+Empty state: "Email integration coming in Phase 3"
+Team
+READ-ONLY
+Display-only — shows seeded team members
+Projects
+Placeholder
+Empty state
+Insights
+Placeholder
+Empty state
+1.2 Authentication
+Set up Clerk (or Auth0) as documented in the Build Environment Setup Guide. Phase 1 is single-user — only Selmen logs in. 2FA required. Session persistence across the PWA (so the user stays logged in for 30 days).
+1.3 Talk Tab — The Continuous Thread
+UI requirements
+	•	Full-screen thread view, mobile-first, scrollable
+	•	Bottom of screen: a sticky input bar with three controls — voice record button (large, primary), text input field, send button
+	•	Voice button: tap-and-hold to record, release to send (iOS/Android pattern). Shows audio waveform while recording.
+	•	Messages from Selmen appear right-aligned, agent responses left-aligned (standard chat pattern)
+	•	Each message shows timestamp on tap
+	•	Voice messages show as a play button with duration; below it, the transcribed text
+	•	Agent's response includes the structured output: "I logged this as a task: [title]. Due: [proposed date]. Tap to edit."
+	•	Pull to refresh for latest
+	•	Thread persists — closing the app and reopening returns to the same scroll position
+Voice flow
+	•	User taps and holds the voice button
+	•	Browser MediaRecorder API captures audio (webm/opus format)
+	•	On release, audio is uploaded to the API
+	•	API stores the file in S3 (or Replit storage), creates a message row with content_type='voice' and the storage URL
+	•	API calls Whisper to transcribe; updates the message with content_text and transcription_confidence
+	•	API calls Claude to parse the transcribed text (intent classification, entity extraction)
+	•	API stores Claude's structured output in claude_parse JSONB column
+	•	API creates downstream artifacts (task row, reminder, etc.) based on parse
+	•	API responds to PWA with the structured result
+	•	PWA renders the user's voice message + transcription + agent's structured response
+Text flow
+Same as voice but skip Whisper. Goes straight to Claude parse.
+1.4 Today Tab — The Brief
+Top section: Daily Brief
+A card at the top shows the current daily brief. Updated automatically at 7 AM and 6 PM. Format:
+GOOD MORNING, SELMEN
+Thursday, May 1, 2026
+
+ON YOUR PLATE TODAY
+  • [3 highest-priority items, briefly]
+
+OVERDUE
+  • [items past due, if any]
+
+CAPTURED OVERNIGHT
+  • [count + summary of what came in since last brief]
+
+AGENT NOTES
+  • [any patterns the agent noticed worth surfacing]
+Briefs are generated by Claude Sonnet, given the prior 12-24 hours of activity. Stored in a briefings table (or as a special row in messages with sender_type='agent', content_type='system').
+Below the brief: Today's List
+A prioritized list of tasks owned by Selmen (owner_id IS NULL). Each row shows:
+	•	Priority badge (urgent / high / normal / low) on the left
+	•	Task title
+	•	Due date if set
+	•	Capture timestamp ("captured 2 hours ago")
+	•	Tap to expand: full description, edit button, mark complete button, delete button
+Below the list: Recent Captures
+Stream of the last 10-20 captured items, including reminders, decisions, and notes (not just tasks). Helps Selmen scan what he's been brain-dumping recently.
+1.5 Capture parsing logic (Claude Sonnet prompt)
+Every capture (voice or text) goes through a Claude call that classifies the input into one of seven types and extracts structured fields. The prompt template:
+SYSTEM:
+You are the parsing layer of Selmen's Chief of Staff agent. Your job is to take
+a captured input and return structured JSON describing what it is and what
+action should be taken.
+
+Selmen is the CEO of Takeovers Rentals. He brain-dumps thoughts throughout
+the day — tasks, reminders, decisions, ideas, questions. You classify each.
+
+Return ONLY a JSON object with this shape:
+{
+  "type": "task" | "reminder" | "decision" | "context" | "question" | "draft_request" | "project",
+  "title": "short summary, max 100 chars",
+  "description": "full structured description",
+  "proposed_owner_hint": null | "team member name if mentioned",
+  "proposed_priority": "urgent" | "high" | "normal" | "low",
+  "proposed_due": null | ISO timestamp,
+  "tags": ["array", "of", "tags"],
+  "requires_clarification": boolean,
+  "clarification_question": null | "question to ask Selmen"
+}
+
+USER:
+Captured input: "{transcribed_text}"
+
+Recent context (last 5 captures):
+{recent_captures_json}
+In Phase 1, the agent does NOT yet act on proposed_owner_hint — that's Phase 2's job. The hint is captured in the database for later use.
+1.6 SMS-to-Agent (Twilio)
+In parallel to the PWA, Selmen can text the agent's dedicated Twilio number. Setup:
+	•	Provision a Twilio number for the agent (production-only Twilio number; staging uses its own)
+	•	Configure the Twilio number's webhook to POST to /api/webhooks/twilio/sms-inbound
+	•	Webhook handler validates the Twilio signature, parses the inbound message, and routes it through the same capture pipeline as PWA input
+	•	If the message is MMS containing audio, download the media URL, store, transcribe via Whisper
+	•	After parsing, the agent replies via SMS with the structured confirmation ("Logged: [task title]. View in app.")
+Webhook handler skeleton
+// apps/api/src/routes/webhooks.ts
+router.post('/webhooks/twilio/sms-inbound',
+  twilioSignatureMiddleware,
+  async (req, res) => {
+    const { From, Body, MediaUrl0, NumMedia } = req.body;
+
+    // Verify From matches Selmen's phone (single-user system)
+    if (From !== process.env.PRINCIPAL_PHONE) {
+      return res.status(403).send('Unauthorized sender');
+    }
+
+    // Get or create the principal_talk thread
+    const thread = await getOrCreatePrincipalThread();
+
+    let contentText = Body;
+    let contentUrl = null;
+    let contentType = 'text';
+
+    if (NumMedia > 0 && MediaUrl0) {
+      // Voice memo via MMS
+      contentUrl = await downloadAndStoreMedia(MediaUrl0);
+      contentText = await transcribeWhisper(contentUrl);
+      contentType = 'voice';
+    }
+
+    // Process through capture pipeline
+    const result = await processCapture({
+      threadId: thread.id,
+      contentText,
+      contentUrl,
+      contentType,
+      direction: 'inbound',
+      senderType: 'principal'
+    });
+
+    // Reply via SMS with structured confirmation
+    return res.type('text/xml').send(
+      buildTwiMLResponse(result.confirmationMessage)
+    );
+  }
+);
+
+2. Tech Decisions for This Phase
+PWA framework
+	•	React + Vite + Tailwind + shadcn/ui (per Master Spec)
+	•	PWA capability via vite-plugin-pwa — manifest, service worker, install prompt
+	•	State management: TanStack Query for server state, Zustand for ephemeral UI state
+	•	Router: React Router v6, single-page app
+Backend
+	•	Node.js + Express 
+	•	Drizzle ORM for Postgres queries — typed end-to-end
+	•	BullMQ for background jobs (briefing generation, Whisper transcription queue)
+	•	Zod for input validation on all API endpoints
+Voice handling
+	•	Browser: MediaRecorder API, captures webm/opus
+	•	Storage: S3-compatible bucket (Replit Object Storage or AWS S3)
+	•	Transcription: OpenAI Whisper API, model whisper-1
+	•	Max recording length: 10 minutes (Whisper handles up to 25MB)
+Claude integration
+	•	Model for parse: claude-sonnet-4-6 (cheap, fast, sufficient for classification)
+	•	Model for daily brief: claude-sonnet-4-6
+	•	Max input tokens per parse: 8K (transcription + recent context)
+	•	Streaming: Not needed in Phase 1 (responses are short)
+
+3. API Endpoints to Build
+3.1 Capture endpoints
+POST   /api/capture                  // Submit a text capture
+POST   /api/capture/voice            // Upload voice memo, returns task ID
+GET    /api/capture/voice/:id        // Poll status (transcribing | parsed | done)
