+
+4. Background Jobs
+4.1 Daily briefing job
+	•	Schedule: 0 7 * * * (7 AM local) and 0 18 * * * (6 PM local)
+	•	Action: Query last 12-24h of captures, recent task changes, send to Claude with the briefing prompt template, store result as a system message in the principal thread
+	•	Push notification: Send web push (and SMS fallback if Selmen hasn't opened the PWA in 4+ hours)
+4.2 Voice transcription queue
+When a voice memo arrives via PWA or MMS, push a job to BullMQ. The worker downloads from storage, calls Whisper, updates the message row, then triggers Claude parse. Async processing prevents the user from waiting on the HTTP request.
+4.3 Whisper retry logic
+	•	If Whisper returns an error, retry up to 3 times with exponential backoff
+	•	If still failing, mark message with transcription_confidence = 0 and a content_text of "[transcription failed - tap to retry]"
+	•	Log to agent_actions_log with success=false
+
