+6. Testing Plan
+6.1 Unit tests
+	•	Capture parser: feed it 50 example transcriptions, assert classification correctness >= 90%
+	•	Brief generator: feed it sample data sets, verify output structure
+	•	Twilio signature validator: positive and negative cases
+	•	Database operations: CRUD on every Phase 1 table
+6.2 Integration tests
+	•	End-to-end voice capture: upload → transcribe → parse → store → retrieve
+	•	End-to-end SMS capture: webhook → parse → store → reply
+	•	Daily brief generation against fixture data
+	•	Auth flow: login → token refresh → session expiry
+6.3 Manual QA
+Run through this checklist in staging before merging to main:
+	•	Send a voice memo from iPhone — verify everything works
+	•	Send a voice memo from Android — verify
+	•	Send a text capture — verify
+	•	Send an SMS to the staging Twilio number — verify
+	•	Wait for morning brief — verify
+	•	Wait for evening brief — verify
+	•	Mark a task complete — verify it disappears from Today tab
+	•	Edit a task's priority — verify sort order updates
+	•	Test offline: disable wifi mid-capture, verify graceful failure and retry
+6.4 Adversarial tests
+	•	Send a 9-minute voice memo — verify it transcribes correctly
+	•	Send a captured input that's ambiguous ("figure out the thing") — verify Claude returns requires_clarification=true
+	•	Send 20 captures in 30 seconds — verify queue handles burst
+	•	Send a captured input in Spanish — verify transcription works (Whisper is multilingual)
+
+7. Dependencies & Prerequisites
+Before starting Phase 1
+	•	Document 03 (Build Environment Setup) is complete — staging and production environments are deployed
+	•	Database migrations for Phase 1 tables are written and applied (principal, team_members, threads, messages, tasks, agent_actions_log, schedules, feature_flags)
+	•	Twilio account is set up, two numbers provisioned (one staging, one production)
+	•	Anthropic API key is set up with separate keys per environment
+	•	OpenAI API key is set up for Whisper
+	•	S3 bucket(s) configured for voice storage
+	•	Clerk (or Auth0) is configured for the PWA
+Phase 1 has no upstream dependencies on other phases
+Phase 1 is the foundation. Subsequent phases (Dispatch, Email, Chase, Projects, Insights, Files) all build on top of Phase 1's capture pipeline and database tables.
+
+8. Risks & Mitigations
+Risk: Whisper transcription is inaccurate for Selmen's accent or speaking style
+Mitigation: Whisper supports an optional 'prompt' parameter that primes the model with vocabulary hints. Pass a prompt with team member names (Oscar, Nick, Josh, Orlando, Joan, Kathy, Karina, Tahir, Richard, Brandon), business terms (Takeovers, Fareharbor, ATV, UTV, sunflower), and locations (Miami, Dallas, Houston). This dramatically improves accuracy.
+Risk: Claude misclassifies captures, leading to bad task suggestions
+Mitigation: Phase 1 is read-only with respect to actions — the agent only stores and surfaces, it doesn't act. Misclassification just means a task is mis-tagged in the database. Selmen can edit any field. Override events feed the learning loop in Phase 6.
+Risk: Voice memo upload fails on poor cell connection
+Mitigation: Upload to S3 with retry; if fails, store the audio in browser IndexedDB and retry on next foreground. Show a 'queued' status in the thread.
+Risk: PWA install prompt doesn't show on iOS
+Mitigation: iOS doesn't auto-prompt PWA install. Add a manual instruction screen on first visit explaining how to add to Home Screen. This is unfortunate but unavoidable.
+Risk: Twilio webhook latency causes user to send a duplicate
+Mitigation: Inbound SMS handler should respond with TwiML in under 5 seconds. Move heavy work (Whisper transcription, Claude parse) to BullMQ queue, not the webhook synchronous path.
+Risk: Daily brief is generic or low-quality
+Mitigation: The first week of briefs will be rough because the agent has minimal context. This is expected. By week 2-3, with more captures in history, briefs become substantive. Don't tune the prompt aggressively before that — let real data accumulate first.
+
+9. Phase 1 Sign-Off Checklist
+When all of these are checked, Phase 1 is complete and you can move to Phase 2.
+	•	All acceptance criteria in Section 5 verified in staging
+	•	All Section 6 manual QA steps passed
+	•	Database backup script is running daily and verified
+	•	Sentry is capturing errors from staging
+	•	Production environment is provisioned but no flags enabled yet
+	•	Documentation in /docs is up to date with any deviations from this spec
+	•	Selmen has used the staging system for at least 5 consecutive days without major issues
+Once you've used the staging Phase 1 system for a week and you trust the capture loop, you're ready to go live in production with Phase 1 only — talk and today tabs, no agent actions toward team. This gives you immediate value while Phase 2 is being built. The momentum matters.
