+TAKEOVERS CHIEF OF STAFF
+Phase 2
+Dispatch + Team Tab
+Document 05 of 13
+Estimated build time: 2-3 weeks
+Outcome: Tasks reach the right person, in their style, on the right channel.
+
+Phase Goal
+Phase 2 closes the second loop: Dispatch. The agent now takes captured tasks and routes them to team members — drafting briefs in each person's preferred communication style, picking the right channel (SMS or email), and either auto-sending (Tier A) or queuing for approval (Tier B).
+This is also the phase where the Team and Approvals tabs become functional. The Team tab becomes Selmen's reference — one card per person with current tasks, response patterns, and contact history. The Approvals tab is where Tier B drafts wait.
+The first time the agent dispatches a task to Oscar via SMS and Oscar texts back "got it", Phase 2 has delivered its core value.
+What you can do at the end of Phase 2:
+	•	Brain-dump a task — agent identifies the owner, drafts the message in their style, sends or queues based on tier
+	•	Review pending dispatches in the Approvals tab and one-tap approve or edit
+	•	Receive team replies — agent threads them with the task and updates status
+	•	Open a team member's card to see all tasks, last contact, response patterns
+	•	Add a new team member from the PWA, immediately routable
+What is explicitly NOT in this phase:
+	•	No automatic follow-up if a team member goes silent (Phase 4)
+	•	No email reading or replying (Phase 3)
+	•	No project tracking (Phase 5)
+	•	No learning from override patterns (Phase 6)
+
+1. The Dispatch Pipeline
+When a capture is classified as type='task' AND has a proposed_owner_hint OR Claude is confident enough to assign one, the dispatch pipeline runs.
+Pipeline stages
+	•	Owner resolution — match the hint or task content against the team_members table
+	•	Tier classification — determine A (autonomous) vs B (approval needed) vs C (Selmen-only)
+	•	Brief drafting — Claude generates the message in the owner's preferred style
+	•	Channel selection — SMS or email based on owner preferences and task complexity
+	•	Deadline proposal — Claude proposes due_at if not set, based on task type
+	•	Send or queue — Tier A goes out via Twilio/Gmail; Tier B becomes a row in email_drafts or a pending SMS in the Approvals tab
+1.1 Owner resolution
+Owner resolution uses two signals:
+	•	Explicit hint: If Selmen's brain-dump contains a name ("have Nick check the tracking pixels"), Claude extracts proposed_owner_hint='Nick' during capture parsing.
+	•	Responsibility match: If no hint, the agent matches task content against the responsibilities array of each team_member. Example: a task about "check fleet repairs" matches Orlando's fleet_management responsibility.
+If multiple team members match, the agent picks the most specific one. If no clear match, the task stays owned by Selmen and surfaces a soft prompt: "Want me to delegate this? Suggested: Oscar."
+Owner resolution logic (pseudocode)
+function resolveOwner(captureParse, teamMembers) {
+  // 1. Explicit hint
+  if (captureParse.proposed_owner_hint) {
+    const match = teamMembers.find(m =>
+      m.short_name.toLowerCase() === captureParse.proposed_owner_hint.toLowerCase()
+    );
+    if (match) return { owner: match, confidence: 0.95 };
+  }
+
+  // 2. Responsibility match via Claude
+  const matchPrompt = buildOwnerMatchPrompt(captureParse, teamMembers);
+  const result = await claude.complete(matchPrompt);
+  // returns { owner_id, confidence, reasoning }
+
+  if (result.confidence >= 0.7) return { owner: ..., confidence: result.confidence };
+  return { owner: null, confidence: result.confidence, suggestion: ... };
+}
+1.2 Tier classification
+Every dispatch is classified into Tier A, B, or C based on rules:
+Tier
+Trigger conditions
+Behavior
+A
+Internal team member, task type is routine, owner has internal_status (not partner_status, not external_status), owner_resolution_confidence >= 0.85
+Auto-send via SMS or email. Log to agent_actions_log.
+B
+Owner has partner_status=true (Brandon, Richard) OR external_status=true (Karina, legal) OR task involves money/contracts/commitments OR owner_resolution_confidence < 0.85
+Draft into Approvals tab. Push notification to Selmen.
+C
+Task involves scheduling a meeting, hiring/firing, signing documents, financial go/no-go decisions
+Stays on Selmen's plate. Surfaced as reminder, not delegation.
+1.3 Brief drafting
+The agent uses Claude to draft the message in the owner's preferred style. Two style templates:
+Detailed style (for Nick, Josh, Oscar)
+Hey [name],
+
+[2-3 sentence context — why this matters, what's connected to it]
+
+What I need: [clear ask, bulleted if multiple things]
+
+[Any relevant deadline or constraint]
+
+Let me know if you have questions.
+Terse style (for Orlando, Joan, Tahir, Kathy, Karina, Richard, Brandon)
+[Name] — [direct ask]. [Deadline if set].
+Brief drafting prompt
+SYSTEM:
+You are drafting a task message from Selmen Hassen to a member of his team.
+Selmen brain-dumped this: "{capture_text}"
+
+The owner is {owner.full_name}, role: {owner.role_summary}.
+Communication style: {owner.communication_style}
+Preferred channel: {owner.preferred_channel}
+Context notes about {owner.short_name}: {owner.context_notes}
+
+Draft the message in Selmen's voice. Selmen is direct, friendly, never
+overly formal. He uses "hey" not "hello". He doesn't sign messages.
+
+If style is 'detailed': use the detailed template (context, ask, deadline).
+If style is 'terse': use the terse template (one short line).
+
+Return JSON:
+{
+  "channel": "sms" | "email",
+  "subject": null | "if email",
+  "body": "the message",
+  "proposed_due": null | ISO timestamp,
+  "reasoning": "why you chose this channel and style"
+}
+1.4 Channel selection
+Default to SMS. Use email instead if any of these are true:
+	•	Task description is longer than ~300 characters or has multiple distinct asks
+	•	Task is tagged 'tech', 'ads', or 'paper-trail-needed' (Nick gets emails for tech/ads context per Selmen's preference)
+	•	Task is for an external party (partners, legal, broker)
+	•	Task involves attachments or images
+	•	Owner's preferred_channel is 'email'
+1.5 Deadline proposal
+If Selmen didn't specify a deadline, Claude proposes one based on task type and urgency:
+Task signal
+Default proposal
+Override rules
+Urgent fire / customer issue
+Today end-of-day
+If after 6 PM, propose tomorrow morning
+Operational task
+48 hours from now
+Skip weekends if owner doesn't work weekends
+Strategic / planning
+End of week
+If issued Wed-Fri, push to next Monday
+Long-term / research
+2 weeks
+Stays as soft deadline, not hard
+Recurring check-in
+Per the schedule cadence
+Honors timezone
