+2. The Approvals Tab
+Tier B drafts wait here for Selmen's review. Each item is a card.
+Card layout
+	•	Top: recipient name, channel icon (SMS/email), draft channel-specific (subject for email)
+	•	Middle: full draft body in a styled chat-bubble or email preview
+	•	Below: agent's reasoning — "Why I drafted this"
+	•	Bottom row: three buttons — Approve / Edit / Reject
+Actions
+	•	Approve: Sends immediately. Logs to agent_actions_log with principal_overrode=false.
+	•	Edit: Opens an inline editor on body (and subject if email). On save, sends and logs with principal_overrode=true and the diff.
+	•	Reject: Marks the draft rejected. Logs principal_overrode=true with reason. The task stays in 'captured' status (still on Selmen's plate).
+Auto-expiry
+Drafts older than 7 days auto-expire. The task is left in 'captured' status and surfaces in Selmen's Today tab as a reminder.
+Push notification
+When a new draft enters Approvals, send a web push notification (and SMS fallback if Selmen hasn't opened the PWA in 4+ hours). Limit to one push per 30-minute window — batch multiple drafts into one notification ("3 new approvals").
