+3. The Team Tab
+Becomes fully functional in Phase 2.
+Top section: Team grid
+One card per active team member. Card shows:
+	•	Avatar (initials or photo)
+	•	Name and role line
+	•	Current open task count
+	•	Last contact timestamp ("3 hours ago")
+	•	Status indicator (responsive / slow / silent based on response time vs their baseline)
+	•	A subtle dot indicating preferred channel (SMS = green, email = blue)
+Tap a card → Member detail view
+	•	Header: full name, role, location, timezone, working hours
+	•	Quick actions: New Task, Send Message, Edit Profile
+	•	Open tasks list (sorted by due date)
+	•	Completed tasks list (collapsible, sorted by completion date)
+	•	Communication thread — full message history with this person
+	•	Response patterns box — average time to acknowledge, average time to complete, current streak
+	•	Context notes (editable)
+Add Member flow
+	•	Tap "+ Add Member" button on the Team grid
+	•	Form: Full Name, Short Name, Role, Phone, Email, Location, Preferred Channel, Communication Style (detailed/terse), Partner status checkbox, External status checkbox, Context notes
+	•	On save: insert into team_members, the agent immediately picks them up in routing
+	•	If phone is provided, the system sends a one-time intro SMS: "Hey [name] — this is Selmen's assistant. He may be reaching you here for tasks and updates. Save this number."
+Edit Member flow
+Same form pre-filled. Soft-update on save. Old preferences are stored in the agent_actions_log as context for the learning loop ("Selmen changed Nick's preferred channel from SMS to email — pattern noted").
+Deactivate Member flow
+	•	Soft delete via deleted_at timestamp
+	•	Open tasks owned by this member surface as needing reassignment
+	•	Prompt: "Oscar has 4 open tasks. Reassign to: __ or close them."
