+4. Inbound Reply Handling
+When a team member replies to an agent-sent SMS or email, the reply must be threaded back to the originating task and surfaced to Selmen.
+4.1 SMS reply flow
+	•	Twilio webhook fires on inbound SMS to the agent's number
+	•	From-number is matched against team_members.phone — identifies the sender
+	•	If sender is a team member, find the most recent task dispatched to them via SMS
+	•	Append the inbound message to the agent ↔ team thread
+	•	Run Claude classification: is this an acknowledgment, a question, a status update, a blocker, a completion?
+	•	Update task status accordingly: dispatched → acknowledged on first reply, → in_progress on "working on it", → blocked on "can't do this because...", → complete on "done"
+	•	If the reply is a question and the agent has context to answer: draft an auto-reply (Tier A or Tier B based on confidence)
+	•	Surface in Selmen's Today tab if escalation is warranted (Phase 4) or if the reply contains a decision Selmen should see
+4.2 Reply classification prompt
+SYSTEM:
+Classify a team member's reply to a task message.
+
+Original task: "{task.description}"
+Original message: "{original_message.body}"
+Reply: "{reply.body}"
+
+Return JSON:
+{
+  "category": "acknowledgment" | "working_on_it" | "completed" | "blocked" | "question" | "status_update" | "unclear",
+  "new_task_status": "acknowledged" | "in_progress" | "blocked" | "complete" | null,
+  "contains_question": boolean,
+  "question_text": null | "the question",
+  "contains_blocker": boolean,
+  "blocker_text": null | "what's blocking",
+  "escalate_to_selmen": boolean,
+  "escalation_reason": null | "why selmen should see this"
+}
+4.3 Auto-reply rules
+The agent only auto-replies to a team member when ALL of these are true:
+	•	The reply contains a question
+	•	Confidence in the answer is >= 0.85
+	•	Answer is fact-based, not a judgment call
+	•	Question is about logistics, deadlines, or scope clarification — not about a decision
+Otherwise, the question is surfaced as a draft reply in the Approvals tab.
