+5. Tech Decisions for This Phase
+Twilio Programmable Messaging
+	•	Conversations API for thread management (recommended) OR raw Messages API
+	•	Webhook for inbound at /api/webhooks/twilio/sms-inbound (already exists from Phase 1, extended here for team replies)
+	•	Status callbacks for delivery receipts: delivered, failed, undelivered — track in messages.delivered_at
+	•	Rate limiting: Twilio allows 1 msg/sec by default. For burst sends (e.g. weekly check-ins to all 11 team members), queue with BullMQ to space sends 1 second apart
+Gmail OAuth (preview for Phase 3)
+Phase 2 starts using Gmail for sending only — no reading yet. Set up the OAuth flow now so Phase 3 can extend it.
+	•	Three OAuth client configurations (one per Gmail account in production)
+	•	Scope: gmail.send only for Phase 2 — modify.metadata, gmail.readonly etc come in Phase 3
+	•	Encrypted refresh tokens stored in email_accounts table
+Claude usage
+	•	Brief drafting: claude-sonnet-4-6 — fast, cheap, sufficient
+	•	Reply classification: claude-sonnet-4-6 — same
+	•	Owner resolution (when no explicit hint): claude-sonnet-4-6
+	•	Edge cases / complex briefs: claude-opus-4-7 — fall back to Opus when Sonnet returns low confidence
