+11. Risks & Mitigations
+Risk: Agent dispatches a task to the wrong person
+Mitigation: Owner resolution requires confidence >= 0.7 to auto-route. Below that, task stays with Selmen. Tier A only fires at >= 0.85. The first 50 dispatches in production should be reviewed manually after the fact to calibrate the confidence thresholds.
+Risk: Style is wrong (too formal, too casual, doesn't sound like Selmen)
+Mitigation: Drafts that Selmen edits in Approvals contribute to the learning loop in Phase 6. Until Phase 6, the system uses fixed style templates from this document. After Phase 6, edited patterns refine the templates.
+In the first weeks of Phase 2 production, it's expected that Selmen will edit ~30% of Tier B drafts. That's the gold data for the learning loop. Don't be discouraged — that's the system working as designed.
+Risk: Team member doesn't recognize the agent's number
+Mitigation: Send the intro SMS when adding a new member. Selmen should also brief his team in person before going live with Phase 2: "You're going to start getting texts from a number labeled 'Selmen's assistant' — that's still me, just routed through a system. Reply normally."
+Risk: Inbound reply classifier mis-categorizes (e.g. 'done' as ack instead of complete)
+Mitigation: Status transitions are reversible. If Selmen sees a status that's wrong, one tap to correct. Wrong classifications also feed the learning loop.
+Risk: Tier B drafts pile up because Selmen forgets to approve
+Mitigation: Push notification for every new draft, batched. Daily morning brief includes a count of pending approvals. Drafts auto-expire after 7 days. If Approvals piles up consistently, the agent can be tuned to broaden Tier A rules — that's a feature, not a bug.
+Risk: Team member responds to old message thread instead of starting new one
+Mitigation: SMS doesn't have rich threading, so we associate inbound replies with the most recent outbound task in the same conversation. Edge case: rapid-fire dispatches in a short window can confuse threading. Acceptable for Phase 2 — Phase 6 learning will tune.
+
