+5. Outbound Email — Sending
+5.1 Send pipeline
+	•	Validate the email_drafts row is approved (or auto_email_reply_internal is enabled and Tier A allows)
+	•	Construct RFC 822 message: From, To, Cc, Subject, Body, Date, Message-ID
+	•	If reply, set In-Reply-To and References headers from the original message — Gmail's threading depends on this
+	•	Convert to base64url, send via users.messages.send
+	•	Store the returned gmail_message_id back to emails table
+	•	Update email_drafts.sent_at and status='sent'
+	•	Log to agent_actions_log
+5.2 Threading correctness
+If replying to an email, the agent must include In-Reply-To and References headers pointing at the original message ID. Without these, Gmail starts a new thread instead of continuing the existing one. Verify this in testing — it's a common bug.
+5.3 Email signature
+Selmen sets each account's signature once during onboarding. The agent appends the signature to outbound emails based on which account is sending. Stored in email_accounts.config (a JSONB field — extend the schema if not present).
+	•	sel@takeoversrentals.com signature: business signature
+	•	selmen@yourmusicmanager.com signature: minimal — this account rarely sends
+	•	soselman@gmail.com signature: personal — short, casual
+5.4 Send rate limits
+Gmail allows ~500 emails per day per account for free Workspace, more for paid. The agent will never approach that volume, but rate-limit at 30 sends per minute to avoid tripping anti-spam heuristics.
