+7. Tech Decisions for This Phase
+Gmail client library
+	•	googleapis npm package (official) — has Gmail bindings, OAuth helpers, refresh handling
+	•	Alternative: raw fetch against the REST API — simpler but you reimplement auth refresh; not worth it
+Email body parsing
+	•	Gmail returns multipart MIME; parse plaintext + HTML parts
+	•	For HTML, use a library like sanitize-html to strip dangerous content + extract readable text for Claude classification
+	•	Cache the cleaned body in emails.body_cached, refresh on demand
+	•	For long emails, truncate to 8K chars before sending to Claude (most context lives in subject + first ~2K of body)
+Encryption at rest
+	•	OAuth refresh tokens encrypted with AES-256-GCM using ENCRYPTION_KEY from env vars
+	•	Email body cache (body_cached column) is NOT encrypted — it's already in Postgres which is access-controlled
+	•	Voice memo recordings stay in S3 with private ACL; same posture for any email attachments downloaded
+Claude usage
+	•	Classification: claude-sonnet-4-6 — high volume, simple decision
+	•	Draft generation: claude-sonnet-4-6 for routine, claude-opus-4-7 for complex (long, multi-stakeholder, partner-related)
+	•	Cost estimate: If Selmen receives ~200 emails per day across 3 accounts, classification costs ~$2-3/day in Sonnet API. Drafts add another $1-2/day. Total Phase 3 cost: ~$100-150/month.
