+3. Escalations
+3.1 What constitutes an escalation
+	•	Two nudges sent without satisfying response
+	•	Team member explicitly replied 'blocked' — immediate escalation
+	•	Hard deadline (due_at) passed without completion
+	•	Tier B draft has been sitting in Approvals tab for >24 hours
+	•	Important flagged email hasn't been addressed in 48 hours
+	•	A previously-acknowledged task hasn't progressed in N days where N depends on priority
+3.2 Escalation message to Selmen
+Pushed via SMS, also surfaced in Today tab and as a push notification. SMS format:
+ESCALATION
+[task title]
+Owner: [team member]
+Last contact: [time ago]
+[brief context — last 1-2 lines from thread]
+
+Recommended: [agent's suggestion]
+[link to PWA]
+3.3 Recommended action generation
+The agent suggests a next step based on the situation:
+Situation
+Suggested next action
+Team member silent past nudge 2
+Place a phone call. They may be in the field with no signal, or this needs a more direct conversation than text.
+Team member explicitly blocked
+Address the blocker directly. The agent surfaces the blocker text from their reply.
+Hard deadline passed
+Reassign or accept slip. Agent suggests a backup owner if responsibility-match exists.
+Tier B draft sitting in Approvals
+Review and approve, edit, or reject. Surfaces the draft directly.
+Flagged email unaddressed
+Reply, archive, delegate, or convert to task. One-tap actions presented.
