+5. Email Chase Logic
+Phase 4 extends the chase loop to email.
+5.1 Outbound email reply tracking
+When the agent (or Selmen via Approvals) sends an email expecting a reply, a followups row is created with:
+	•	entity_type = 'email_thread'
+	•	expected_response_within = inferred from email content (e.g. "by EOD Friday" → that timestamp; otherwise default 72 hours)
+	•	Cadence: nudge 1 at expected_response_within, nudge 2 at +24h, escalation at +48h
+5.2 Email nudge generation
+Same prompt structure as SMS nudges, but acknowledges email context:
+Hi Brandon,
+
+Just wanted to circle back on the message I sent Tuesday
+about the lawyer intro. No rush — just making sure it
+didn't get buried.
+
+Thanks,
+Selmen
+5.3 Approvals tab nudges
+If a Tier B draft has been sitting in Approvals for >24 hours, the agent sends a self-nudge to Selmen via PWA push notification: "You have 3 drafts waiting more than 24 hours." Daily morning brief includes a count of pending approvals.
+5.4 Flagged email aging
+Important emails the agent flagged for Selmen's eyes age out. After 48 hours unaddressed, they escalate. The escalation prompts: "This was flagged 2 days ago. Want me to draft a reply, or should we just archive?"
