+6. Working Hours & Timezone Handling
+6.1 Team member working hours
+Each team_members row stores working_hours as JSONB. Default if not specified: 8 AM - 8 PM, Monday-Saturday.
+// Example working_hours JSON
+{
+  "start": "08:00",
+  "end": "20:00",
+  "days": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6],   // 0=Sun, 6=Sat
+  "timezone": "America/New_York"
+}
+6.2 Nudge scheduling rules
+	•	Compute scheduled_for timestamp from dispatched_at + cadence offset
+	•	If scheduled_for falls outside the owner's working hours, advance to the next working window's start time
+	•	If scheduled_for falls on a weekend day not in the owner's days array, advance to next valid day
+	•	Cap shift to maximum +18 hours — don't shift a Friday 11 PM nudge all the way to Monday 8 AM, that's too long
+6.3 Timezone special cases
+	•	Richard in Texas: timezone America/Chicago — nudges respect Central Time
+	•	Karina (realtor): respects her stated working hours, never weekends
+	•	Brandon: respects working hours but skews more lenient because he's a partner
+6.4 Selmen's escalations are timezone-respecting too
+Selmen has working hours configured in the principal table. Escalations during off-hours don't push SMS unless the priority is 'urgent'. Otherwise they queue and surface in the morning brief.
