+7. Tech Decisions for This Phase
+Background job framework
+	•	BullMQ + Redis for the follow-up scheduler. Repeatable jobs at 5-minute intervals.
+	•	Alternative: n8n cron node for high-level orchestration, BullMQ for tight scheduling. Both can coexist.
+Followup table queries
+The hot query in Phase 4 runs every 5 minutes:
+SELECT * FROM followups
+WHERE status = 'pending'
+  AND scheduled_for <= NOW()
+ORDER BY scheduled_for ASC
+LIMIT 100;
+The index idx_followups_due (already specified in Document 02) handles this. With 1000s of rows, this query stays under 10ms.
+Working hours computation
+Implement as a utility function that takes (timestamp, working_hours) → adjusted_timestamp. Use a date library — date-fns-tz or luxon. Test the timezone math thoroughly; it's the source of bugs in any scheduling system.
+Claude usage
+	•	Nudge generation: claude-sonnet-4-6 — short, contextual, reuses style preferences
+	•	Escalation recommendation: claude-sonnet-4-6 with full thread context
+	•	Volume: If 30 tasks/week need nudges, that's ~60 Claude calls/week for nudges. Cost: ~$5/month additional.
