+9. Background Jobs
+9.1 Follow-up scheduler (every 5 min)
+Core job. Fetches due followups, generates nudge messages via Claude, sends via Twilio/Gmail, updates status.
+// Pseudocode
+async function processDueFollowups() {
+  const due = await db.select().from(followups)
+    .where(and(
+      eq(followups.status, 'pending'),
+      lte(followups.scheduled_for, new Date())
+    ))
+    .limit(100);
+
+  for (const f of due) {
+    if (f.nudge_level <= 2) {
+      await sendNudge(f);
+    } else {
+      await raiseEscalation(f);
+    }
+  }
+}
+9.2 Working-hours window check (every 1 min)
+Lightweight job that checks if any pending followups should be advanced because they fall outside working hours. Runs more frequently than the main scheduler so windowing decisions are timely.
+9.3 Stale draft sweep (every hour)
+Identifies email_drafts in pending_review status older than 24h, raises a self-nudge to Selmen. Older than 7 days → expire (per Phase 2).
+9.4 Daily chase summary (in morning brief)
+As part of the Phase 1 morning brief job, add an Awaiting section count and any escalations that emerged overnight.
