+13. Risks & Mitigations
+Risk: Agent over-nudges and burns team trust
+Mitigation: Hard cap of 2 team-facing nudges per task. After that, escalation goes to Selmen, not more nudges to the team. Cadence respects working hours. Style is friendly, never passive-aggressive (verified in nudge prompt). If a team member ever expresses frustration with nudges, that signal can manually adjust their cadence preference.
+Risk: Team member responds informally and reply classifier misses it
+Mitigation: Reply classifier was tested in Phase 2. Edge cases ("k" for okay, "yup" for yes, emoji-only replies) are in the test fixture. If a reply is unclear, classifier returns 'unclear' and the agent keeps the chase clock running but doesn't escalate yet — surfaces in Today tab so Selmen can manually mark resolved.
+Risk: Timezone bugs cause off-hours messages
+Mitigation: Timezone math is the most-tested component of Phase 4. Use a battle-tested library (luxon or date-fns-tz). Set up a smoke test that runs hourly, verifying the next 5 scheduled nudges all fall within their owner's working hours.
+Risk: Escalation fires for trivial silence (someone is on vacation)
+Mitigation: Vacation/OOO support is post-Phase-4. For now, Selmen can manually mark a team member as 'on leave' which pauses chase on tasks owned by them. Phase 6 learning may detect patterns ("Joan tends to be slow on Sundays") and adjust automatically.
+Risk: System clock drift or job worker outage causes missed nudges
+Mitigation: Scheduler is idempotent — re-running it picks up missed work. Sentry alerts if BullMQ queue depth grows. If a worker is down for >15 minutes, alert via SMS to Selmen so he knows the agent is delayed.
+Risk: Selmen approves all his Approvals at once and all nudges fire simultaneously
+Mitigation: Approving 10 drafts at once enqueues 10 outbound sends, throttled by the rate limiter (1 SMS/sec via Twilio rate limit, 30 emails/min). Recipients receive within 30 seconds, not in a burst. The 10 followups are also created spaced out so future nudges don't fire as a burst either.
