+11. Testing Plan
+11.1 Unit tests
+	•	Project detection classifier: feed 30 brain-dumps, verify >80% accuracy on project vs. task
+	•	Dependency check: tests covering empty deps, single dep, multiple deps, deep chains
+	•	Risk auto-adjustment: every transition rule covered
+	•	Milestone snapshot regeneration: each task state change triggers correct snapshot update
+11.2 Integration tests
+	•	Full project lifecycle: brain-dump → detection → planning → approval → dispatch → completion → archive
+	•	Pause and resume across milestone boundaries
+	•	Cancel mid-flight: verify no further dispatches
+	•	Adding/removing milestones to active project
+	•	Risk escalation: trigger every transition path
+11.3 Behavior tests against shadow team
+	•	Run a real-feeling Fareharbor-style project end-to-end in staging. 5 days, multiple team members. Verify the agent's project-level observations track real progress.
+	•	Have one shadow team member intentionally stall a milestone. Verify risk elevates and downstream milestones reflect blocked-upstream state.
+	•	Complete a project. Verify archive correctness — final state captured, all timestamps in place.
+11.4 Adversarial tests
+	•	Circular dependencies (M1 depends on M2, M2 depends on M1) — verify detection and rejection during planning
+	•	Project with 50 milestones — verify performance
+	•	Two projects sharing same owner with overlapping deadlines — verify the agent flags the conflict
+	•	Brain-dump that's a project but with vague description — verify clarification request
