+Phase Goal
+Phase 7 expands the agent's reach in two complementary directions. First, Google Drive integration so the agent can read, create, organize, and share files — covering the bulk of "can you find that doc" or "create a new one-pager about X" requests without dropping into local computer access. Second, GitHub integration so the agent has live context on Selmen's tech stack — when Nick or Tahir get a task referencing "the tracking script" or "the FareHarbor webhook", the agent can pull the actual file and ground the task brief in real code instead of generalities.
+Both integrations are read-write but bounded. Drive starts read-write but only in folders Selmen has explicitly granted. GitHub starts read-only — write access (opening issues, commenting on PRs) can be added later if Selmen wants. This phase intentionally avoids local computer access. Most file operations are cloud-based and Drive covers them; local access opens a security surface that isn't worth it until there's a specific unmet need.
+What you can do at the end of Phase 7:
+	•	Brain-dump references a file ("can you pull up the Q2 marketing plan") and the agent finds it in Drive
+	•	Brain-dump asks for a new doc ("draft a one-pager on the new pricing structure") and the agent creates it
+	•	Tech task references code ("have Nick fix the bug in the FareHarbor webhook") and the agent pulls the relevant file as context for the dispatch brief
+	•	Agent responds to questions about codebase state ("what's the current pixel ID in production?") by reading the repo
+	•	Agent can attach Drive files to outbound emails when needed
+	•	Agent links to specific files or commits in task briefs to give team members direct context
+What is explicitly NOT in this phase:
+	•	No write access to GitHub repos (no committing, no opening PRs, no editing files)
+	•	No local computer access — Drive only for cloud files
+	•	No Drive bulk operations (no "organize all my files" — too risky)
+	•	No automated code review or technical analysis (the agent reads code for context, not to judge it)
