+1. Google Drive Integration
+1.1 OAuth setup
+Drive uses the same Google Cloud project as Gmail (Phase 3). Add Drive scopes to the existing OAuth consent screen. The agent connects to one Drive account — Selmen's primary work Drive (associated with sel@takeoversrentals.com).
+Required scopes
+https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.file
+// Lets the agent access only files it created OR files explicitly opened
+// via Drive picker. Most secure default.
+
+https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.metadata.readonly
+// Read file metadata (titles, owners, dates) for search
+
+// NOT used by default:
+// drive (full access) — too broad
+// drive.readonly — too broad
+The drive.file scope is much safer than drive.readonly. It restricts the agent to files Selmen has explicitly granted access to via Drive picker, plus files the agent itself created. This means a malicious prompt cannot trick the agent into exfiltrating arbitrary Drive content. Strongly recommended.
+1.2 Folder authorization model
+Selmen explicitly grants the agent access to specific folders via a one-time setup flow:
+	•	In PWA Settings → Drive Access, tap "Authorize a folder"
+	•	Drive picker opens — Selmen selects a folder (e.g. "Takeovers Operations")
+	•	Agent stores the folder ID in drive_folders table
+	•	Agent has full access (read + create + update) within that folder and its subfolders
+Recommended folder authorizations
+	•	Takeovers Operations folder — operational documents, SOPs, training materials
+	•	Marketing folder — marketing plans, creative briefs, ad copy
+	•	Templates folder — reusable templates for common documents
+	•	Reports folder — generated reports the agent might create
+	•	Selmen explicitly does NOT authorize: financial documents, legal documents, anything personal
+1.3 File operations the agent supports
+Operation
+Authority
+Use case
+Search by title/content
+Tier A within authorized folders
+"Find the Q2 marketing plan"
+Open and read a file
+Tier A within authorized folders
+Pull file content for context in dispatch or response
+Create a new doc
+Tier A in agreed-upon target folder
+"Draft a one-pager on the new pricing"
+Update an existing doc
+Tier B (always drafts edit, never auto-applies)
+"Update the Q2 plan with the new numbers"
+Move/rename a file
+Tier B
+Organizational changes need approval
+Delete a file
+Tier C (Selmen does it himself)
+Agent never deletes — only suggests
+Share a file externally
