+Inherits authority from the email it's attached to
+1.4 File creation flow
+When Selmen says "draft a one-pager on the new pricing structure", the agent:
+	•	Determines the doc type (one-pager → Google Doc; spreadsheet → Sheet; presentation → Slides)
+	•	Identifies the target folder (default: "Takeovers Operations" unless context suggests otherwise)
+	•	Generates the content via Claude (using existing context — recent threads, related files)
+	•	Creates the file via Drive API
+	•	Returns a confirmation in the Talk tab with the file link
+	•	Optionally adds the link to a related task or email
+File creation prompt (for content generation)
+SYSTEM:
+Generate the content of a {doc_type} for Selmen Hassen.
+
+Selmen requested: "{request_text}"
+
+Relevant context from recent threads:
+{recent_context}
+
+Format:
+  - One-pager: short, scannable, headline + 3-5 bullet sections
+  - Internal memo: header, context, recommendation, next steps
+  - Marketing brief: audience, message, channels, success metrics
+  - SOP: numbered steps with owner per step
+
+Selmen's voice: direct, concrete, no fluff.
+
+Return ONLY the document body content. No commentary.
+1.5 File search flow
+When Selmen says "pull up the Fareharbor migration plan":
+	•	Agent queries Drive API search across authorized folders
+	•	Search query: title contains "fareharbor" OR fullText contains "fareharbor migration"
+	•	Returns top 5 candidates with metadata (title, modified date, owner)
+	•	Agent surfaces results in Talk tab: "Found 3 matches — here they are with links"
+	•	If only one strong match, agent can read its content for use in current context
